TFF exports patch: fix missing symbols in libtensorflow_cc.so
=============================================================

TensorFlow's own pip package build uses `pywrap_rules` which bypasses the
`cc_shared_library` mechanism entirely (see `tf_cc_shared_library_opensource`
in tensorflow.bzl — it early-returns when `use_pywrap_rules()` is true).

TFF, however, consumes TF as an external dependency via `cc_shared_library`,
which builds `libtensorflow_cc.so` using a `roots` attribute to determine
which symbols to export. Any symbol whose defining target is not listed in
`roots` (directly or transitively) gets stripped from the shared library by
the linker, even if other code *inside* the same .so references it.

This patch works around those gaps. The three symbol groups fixed here:

  kernel_shape_util: GetWindowedOutputSize, GetWindowedOutputSizeVerbose,
    Get3dOutputSizeV2 — referenced by nn_ops, conv_ops, conv_ops_3d, and
    array_ops shape functions/kernels inside TF.

  wav_io: EncodeAudioAsS16LEWav, DecodeLin16WaveAsFloatVector — referenced
    by summary_audio_op, encode_wav_op, and decode_wav_op kernels inside TF.

  percentile_sampler: PercentileSamplerCell — referenced by
    batch_resource_base (TF serving batching) inside TF.

